THE Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Kano State chapter has confirmed that an accident which occured in the early hours of Wednesday claimed the lives of 12 persons while 26 persons sustained various degree of injuries. It would be recalled that an eyewitness told Tribune Online that many people lost their lives in the accident that occurred in Tsaida village near Gaya town in Kano State around 11 am. Those who sustained injuries and the remains of the dead victims have been taken to Gaya General Hospital. Trade union lauds Ganduje over minimum wage implementation Zamfara: Two killed, 12 others injured in road crash Yuletide: FRSC deploys 605 officers, marshals in Gombe Yuletide: FRSC deploys 801 personnel for special operation… ALSO READ: Re-run elections: PDP questions Buhari’s meeting with INEC boss, IGP A reliable source disclosed that the accident involved three vehicles including a bus and two other saloon cars. Information provided by the Public Relation Officer (PRO) of the corps the state, Kabir Daura, said 38 people were involved in the accident. He listed the vehicles involved in the accident to include a V/W Golf and a Haice (Hummer), with registration number BBR690AA and KTG467YG, respectively. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NEW MAN MACHINE